36static u32
37read_div(struct nv50_clk *clk)
38{
39 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
40 switch (device->chipset) {
41 case 0x50: /* it exists, but only has bit 31, not the dividers.. */
42 case 0x84:
43 case 0x86:
44 case 0x98:
45 case 0xa0:
46 return nvkm_rd32(device, 0x004700);
47 case 0x92:
48 case 0x94:
49 case 0x96:
50 return nvkm_rd32(device, 0x004800);
51 default:
52 return 0x00000000;
53 }
54}
55
56static u32
57read_pll_src(struct nv50_clk *clk, u32 base)
58{
59 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->base.subdev;
60 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
61 u32 coef, ref = nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_crystal);
62 u32 rsel = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e18c);
63 int P, N, M, id;
64
65 switch (device->chipset) {
66 case 0x50:
67 case 0xa0:
68 switch (base) {
69 case 0x4020:
70 case 0x4028: id = !!(rsel & 0x00000004); break;
71 case 0x4008: id = !!(rsel & 0x00000008); break;
72 case 0x4030: id = 0; break;
73 default:
74 nvkm_error(subdev, "ref: bad pll %06x\n", base);
75 return 0;
76 }
77
78 coef = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e81c + (id * 0x0c));
79 ref *= (coef & 0x01000000) ? 2 : 4;
80 P = (coef & 0x00070000) >> 16;
81 N = ((coef & 0x0000ff00) >> 8) + 1;
82 M = ((coef & 0x000000ff) >> 0) + 1;
83 break;
84 case 0x84:
85 case 0x86:
86 case 0x92:
87 coef = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e81c);
88 P = (coef & 0x00070000) >> 16;
89 N = (coef & 0x0000ff00) >> 8;
90 M = (coef & 0x000000ff) >> 0;
91 break;
92 case 0x94:
93 case 0x96:
94 case 0x98:
95 rsel = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00c050);
96 switch (base) {
97 case 0x4020: rsel = (rsel & 0x00000003) >> 0; break;
98 case 0x4008: rsel = (rsel & 0x0000000c) >> 2; break;
99 case 0x4028: rsel = (rsel & 0x00001800) >> 11; break;
100 case 0x4030: rsel = 3; break;
101 default:
102 nvkm_error(subdev, "ref: bad pll %06x\n", base);
103 return 0;
104 }
105
106 switch (rsel) {
107 case 0: id = 1; break;
108 case 1: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_crystal);
109 case 2: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_href);
110 case 3: id = 0; break;
111 }
112
113 coef = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e81c + (id * 0x28));
114 P = (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e824 + (id * 0x28)) >> 16) & 7;
115 P += (coef & 0x00070000) >> 16;
116 N = (coef & 0x0000ff00) >> 8;
117 M = (coef & 0x000000ff) >> 0;
118 break;
119 default:
120 BUG_ON(1);
121 M = 0; /* XXX GCC is stupid */
122 N = 0; /* XXX GCC is stupid */
123 P = 0; /* XXX GCC is stupid */
124 }
125
126 if (M)
127 return (ref * N / M) >> P;
128
129 return 0;
130}
131
132static u32
133read_pll_ref(struct nv50_clk *clk, u32 base)
134{
135 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->base.subdev;
136 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
137 u32 src, mast = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00c040);
138
139 switch (base) {
140 case 0x004028:
141 src = !!(mast & 0x00200000);
142 break;
143 case 0x004020:
144 src = !!(mast & 0x00400000);
145 break;
146 case 0x004008:
147 src = !!(mast & 0x00010000);
148 break;
149 case 0x004030:
150 src = !!(mast & 0x02000000);
151 break;
152 case 0x00e810:
153 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_crystal);
154 default:
155 nvkm_error(subdev, "bad pll %06x\n", base);
156 return 0;
157 }
158
159 if (src)
160 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_href);
161
162 return read_pll_src(clk, base);
163}
164
165static u32
166read_pll(struct nv50_clk *clk, u32 base)
167{
168 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
169 u32 mast = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00c040);
170 u32 ctrl = nvkm_rd32(device, base + 0);
171 u32 coef = nvkm_rd32(device, base + 4);
172 u32 ref = read_pll_ref(clk, base);
173 u32 freq = 0;
174 int N1, N2, M1, M2;
175
176 if (base == 0x004028 && (mast & 0x00100000)) {
177 /* wtf, appears to only disable post-divider on gt200 */
178 if (device->chipset != 0xa0)
179 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_dom6);
180 }
181
182 N2 = (coef & 0xff000000) >> 24;
183 M2 = (coef & 0x00ff0000) >> 16;
184 N1 = (coef & 0x0000ff00) >> 8;
185 M1 = (coef & 0x000000ff);
186 if ((ctrl & 0x80000000) && M1) {
187 freq = ref * N1 / M1;
188 if ((ctrl & 0x40000100) == 0x40000000) {
189 if (M2)
190 freq = freq * N2 / M2;
191 else
192 freq = 0;
193 }
194 }
195
196 return freq;
197}
198
199int
200nv50_clk_read(struct nvkm_clk *base, enum nv_clk_src src)
201{
202 struct nv50_clk *clk = nv50_clk(base);
203 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->base.subdev;
204 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
205 u32 mast = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00c040);
206 u32 P = 0;
207
208 switch (src) {
209 case nv_clk_src_crystal:
210 return device->crystal;
211 case nv_clk_src_href:
212 return 100000; /* PCIE reference clock */
213 case nv_clk_src_hclk:
214 return div_u64((u64)nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_href) * 27778, 10000);
215 case nv_clk_src_hclkm3:
216 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclk) * 3;
217 case nv_clk_src_hclkm3d2:
218 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclk) * 3 / 2;
219 case nv_clk_src_host:
220 switch (mast & 0x30000000) {
221 case 0x00000000: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_href);
222 case 0x10000000: break;
223 case 0x20000000: /* !0x50 */
224 case 0x30000000: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclk);
225 }
226 break;
227 case nv_clk_src_core:
228 if (!(mast & 0x00100000))
229 P = (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x004028) & 0x00070000) >> 16;
230 switch (mast & 0x00000003) {
231 case 0x00000000: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_crystal) >> P;
232 case 0x00000001: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_dom6);
233 case 0x00000002: return read_pll(clk, 0x004020) >> P;
234 case 0x00000003: return read_pll(clk, 0x004028) >> P;
235 }
236 break;
237 case nv_clk_src_shader:
238 P = (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x004020) & 0x00070000) >> 16;
239 switch (mast & 0x00000030) {
240 case 0x00000000:
241 if (mast & 0x00000080)
242 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_host) >> P;
243 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_crystal) >> P;
244 case 0x00000010: break;
245 case 0x00000020: return read_pll(clk, 0x004028) >> P;
246 case 0x00000030: return read_pll(clk, 0x004020) >> P;
247 }
248 break;
249 case nv_clk_src_mem:
250 P = (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x004008) & 0x00070000) >> 16;
251 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x004008) & 0x00000200) {
252 switch (mast & 0x0000c000) {
253 case 0x00000000:
254 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_crystal) >> P;
255 case 0x00008000:
256 case 0x0000c000:
257 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_href) >> P;
258 }
259 } else {
260 return read_pll(clk, 0x004008) >> P;
261 }
262 break;
263 case nv_clk_src_vdec:
264 P = (read_div(clk) & 0x00000700) >> 8;
265 switch (device->chipset) {
266 case 0x84:
267 case 0x86:
268 case 0x92:
269 case 0x94:
270 case 0x96:
271 case 0xa0:
272 switch (mast & 0x00000c00) {
273 case 0x00000000:
274 if (device->chipset == 0xa0) /* wtf?? */
275 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_core) >> P;
276 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_crystal) >> P;
277 case 0x00000400:
278 return 0;
279 case 0x00000800:
280 if (mast & 0x01000000)
281 return read_pll(clk, 0x004028) >> P;
282 return read_pll(clk, 0x004030) >> P;
283 case 0x00000c00:
284 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_core) >> P;
285 }
286 break;
287 case 0x98:
288 switch (mast & 0x00000c00) {
289 case 0x00000000:
290 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_core) >> P;
291 case 0x00000400:
292 return 0;
293 case 0x00000800:
294 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclkm3d2) >> P;
295 case 0x00000c00:
296 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_mem) >> P;
297 }
298 break;
299 }
300 break;
301 case nv_clk_src_dom6:
302 switch (device->chipset) {
303 case 0x50:
304 case 0xa0:
305 return read_pll(clk, 0x00e810) >> 2;
306 case 0x84:
307 case 0x86:
308 case 0x92:
309 case 0x94:
310 case 0x96:
311 case 0x98:
312 P = (read_div(clk) & 0x00000007) >> 0;
313 switch (mast & 0x0c000000) {
314 case 0x00000000: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_href);
315 case 0x04000000: break;
316 case 0x08000000: return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclk);
317 case 0x0c000000:
318 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclkm3) >> P;
319 }
320 break;
321 default:
322 break;
323 }
324 default:
325 break;
326 }
327
328 nvkm_debug(subdev, "unknown clock source %d %08x\n", src, mast);
329 return -EINVAL;
330}
331
332static u32
333calc_pll(struct nv50_clk *clk, u32 reg, u32 idx, int *N, int *M, int *P)
334{
335 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->base.subdev;
336 struct nvbios_pll pll;
337 int ret;
338
339 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(subdev->device->bios, reg, &pll);
340 if (ret)
341 return 0;
342
343 pll.vco2.max_freq = 0;
344 pll.refclk = read_pll_ref(clk, reg);
345 if (!pll.refclk)
346 return 0;
347
348 return nv04_pll_calc(subdev, &pll, idx, N, M, NULL, NULL, P);
349}
350
351static inline u32
352calc_div(u32 src, u32 target, int *div)
353{
354 u32 clk0 = src, clk1 = src;
355 for (*div = 0; *div <= 7; (*div)++) {
356 if (clk0 <= target) {
357 clk1 = clk0 << (*div ? 1 : 0);
358 break;
359 }
360 clk0 >>= 1;
361 }
362
363 if (target - clk0 <= clk1 - target)
364 return clk0;
365 (*div)--;
366 return clk1;
367}
368
369static inline u32
370clk_same(u32 a, u32 b)
371{
372 return ((a / 1000) == (b / 1000));
373}
374
375int
376nv50_clk_calc(struct nvkm_clk *base, struct nvkm_cstate *cstate)
377{
378 struct nv50_clk *clk = nv50_clk(base);
379 struct nv50_clk_hwsq *hwsq = &clk->hwsq;
380 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->base.subdev;
381 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
382 const int shader = cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_shader];
383 const int core = cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_core];
384 const int vdec = cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_vdec];
385 const int dom6 = cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_dom6];
386 u32 mastm = 0, mastv = 0;
387 u32 divsm = 0, divsv = 0;
388 int N, M, P1, P2;
389 int freq, out;
390
391 /* prepare a hwsq script from which we'll perform the reclock */
392 out = clk_init(hwsq, subdev);
393 if (out)
394 return out;
395
396 clk_wr32(hwsq, fifo, 0x00000001); /* block fifo */
397 clk_nsec(hwsq, 8000);
398 clk_setf(hwsq, 0x10, 0x00); /* disable fb */
399 clk_wait(hwsq, 0x00, 0x01); /* wait for fb disabled */
400
401 /* vdec: avoid modifying xpll until we know exactly how the other
402 * clock domains work, i suspect at least some of them can also be
403 * tied to xpll...
404 */
405 if (vdec) {
406 /* see how close we can get using nvclk as a source */
407 freq = calc_div(core, vdec, &P1);
408
409 /* see how close we can get using xpll/hclk as a source */
410 if (device->chipset != 0x98)
411 out = read_pll(clk, 0x004030);
412 else
413 out = nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclkm3d2);
414 out = calc_div(out, vdec, &P2);
415
416 /* select whichever gets us closest */
417 if (abs(vdec - freq) <= abs(vdec - out)) {
418 if (device->chipset != 0x98)
419 mastv |= 0x00000c00;
420 divsv |= P1 << 8;
421 } else {
422 mastv |= 0x00000800;
423 divsv |= P2 << 8;
424 }
425
426 mastm |= 0x00000c00;
427 divsm |= 0x00000700;
428 }
429
430 /* dom6: nfi what this is, but we're limited to various combinations
431 * of the host clock frequency
432 */
433 if (dom6) {
434 if (clk_same(dom6, nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_href))) {
435 mastv |= 0x00000000;
436 } else
437 if (clk_same(dom6, nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclk))) {
438 mastv |= 0x08000000;
439 } else {
440 freq = nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_hclk) * 3;
441 calc_div(freq, dom6, &P1);
442
443 mastv |= 0x0c000000;
444 divsv |= P1;
445 }
446
447 mastm |= 0x0c000000;
448 divsm |= 0x00000007;
449 }
450
451 /* vdec/dom6: switch to "safe" clocks temporarily, update dividers
452 * and then switch to target clocks
453 */
454 clk_mask(hwsq, mast, mastm, 0x00000000);
455 clk_mask(hwsq, divs, divsm, divsv);
456 clk_mask(hwsq, mast, mastm, mastv);
457
458 /* core/shader: disconnect nvclk/sclk from their PLLs (nvclk to dom6,
459 * sclk to hclk) before reprogramming
460 */
461 if (device->chipset < 0x92)
462 clk_mask(hwsq, mast, 0x001000b0, 0x00100080);
463 else
464 clk_mask(hwsq, mast, 0x000000b3, 0x00000081);
465
466 /* core: for the moment at least, always use nvpll */
467 freq = calc_pll(clk, 0x4028, core, &N, &M, &P1);
468 if (freq == 0)
469 return -ERANGE;
470
471 clk_mask(hwsq, nvpll[0], 0xc03f0100,
472 0x80000000 | (P1 << 19) | (P1 << 16));
473 clk_mask(hwsq, nvpll[1], 0x0000ffff, (N << 8) | M);
474
475 /* shader: tie to nvclk if possible, otherwise use spll. have to be
476 * very careful that the shader clock is at least twice the core, or
477 * some chipsets will be very unhappy. i expect most or all of these
478 * cases will be handled by tying to nvclk, but it's possible there's
479 * corners
480 */
481 if (P1-- && shader == (core << 1)) {
482 clk_mask(hwsq, spll[0], 0xc03f0100, (P1 << 19) | (P1 << 16));
483 clk_mask(hwsq, mast, 0x00100033, 0x00000023);
484 } else {
485 freq = calc_pll(clk, 0x4020, shader, &N, &M, &P1);
486 if (freq == 0)
487 return -ERANGE;
488
489 clk_mask(hwsq, spll[0], 0xc03f0100,
490 0x80000000 | (P1 << 19) | (P1 << 16));
491 clk_mask(hwsq, spll[1], 0x0000ffff, (N << 8) | M);
492 clk_mask(hwsq, mast, 0x00100033, 0x00000033);
493 }
494
495 /* restore normal operation */
496 clk_setf(hwsq, 0x10, 0x01); /* enable fb */
497 clk_wait(hwsq, 0x00, 0x00); /* wait for fb enabled */
498 clk_wr32(hwsq, fifo, 0x00000000); /* un-block fifo */
499 return 0;
500}
501
502int
503nv50_clk_prog(struct nvkm_clk *base)
504{
505 struct nv50_clk *clk = nv50_clk(base);
506 return clk_exec(&clk->hwsq, true);
507}
508
509void
510nv50_clk_tidy(struct nvkm_clk *base)
511{
512 struct nv50_clk *clk = nv50_clk(base);
513 clk_exec(&clk->hwsq, false);
514}
515
516int
517nv50_clk_new_(const struct nvkm_clk_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
518 int index, bool allow_reclock, struct nvkm_clk **pclk)
519{
520 struct nv50_clk *clk;
521 int ret;
522
523 if (!(clk = kzalloc(sizeof(*clk), GFP_KERNEL)))
524 return -ENOMEM;
525 ret = nvkm_clk_ctor(func, device, index, allow_reclock, &clk->base);
526 *pclk = &clk->base;
527 if (ret)
528 return ret;
529
530 clk->hwsq.r_fifo = hwsq_reg(0x002504);
531 clk->hwsq.r_spll[0] = hwsq_reg(0x004020);
532 clk->hwsq.r_spll[1] = hwsq_reg(0x004024);
533 clk->hwsq.r_nvpll[0] = hwsq_reg(0x004028);
534 clk->hwsq.r_nvpll[1] = hwsq_reg(0x00402c);
535 switch (device->chipset) {
536 case 0x92:
537 case 0x94:
538 case 0x96:
539 clk->hwsq.r_divs = hwsq_reg(0x004800);
540 break;
541 default:
542 clk->hwsq.r_divs = hwsq_reg(0x004700);
543 break;
544 }
545 clk->hwsq.r_mast = hwsq_reg(0x00c040);
546 return 0;
547}
548
549static const struct nvkm_clk_func
550nv50_clk = {
551 .read = nv50_clk_read,
552 .calc = nv50_clk_calc,
553 .prog = nv50_clk_prog,
554 .tidy = nv50_clk_tidy,
555 .domains = {
556 { nv_clk_src_crystal, 0xff },
557 { nv_clk_src_href , 0xff },
558 { nv_clk_src_core , 0xff, 0, "core", 1000 },
559 { nv_clk_src_shader , 0xff, 0, "shader", 1000 },
560 { nv_clk_src_mem , 0xff, 0, "memory", 1000 },
561 { nv_clk_src_max }
562 }
563};
564
565int
566nv50_clk_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_clk **pclk)
567{
568 return nv50_clk_new_(&nv50_clk, device, index, false, pclk);
569}
